This paper deals with the security of interaction protocols, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also uses game theory concepts to analyze the incentives of participants, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.GT (game theory). The paper also proposes the use of defender sets, which is a concept that falls under the category of distributed systems (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper presents theoretical characterizations of defendable protocols, which could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) or cryptography (cs.CY).
